Subscription in azure is like credit card without any limit. We won’t be charged until the end of the month.
Different ways to get subscription
	Free trail subscription- we can use until 200$ worth services.
	Pay as you go subscription- Comes after free trail is over
	MSDN subscription- Microsoft developer network
	EA Subscription- Enterprise Agreement- Subscription happens through enrollment. 
Portal.azure.com
Activity log, Resource group
Resource group is like a container. Storing resources. Like a separate workspace.
Identity Access Management(IAM)
RBAC roles- Role based access control- There are 800+ built-in roles for 200+services.
Based on role we will limit the access. We can also create custom role
Tags we use for billing purpose
Cost Analysis- Which services utilizing how much. Can be viewed at Resource group level and subscription level.
